Senior Engineer (Building background) Dutco Balfour Beatty (DBB)Dubai, UAERef: OP085-08The RoleThe RoleSUMMARY (Brief summary of the position): At the direction of the Principle Engineer, responsible for ensuring that works are being constructed in accordance with the drawings and specification as per contract requirements and companyâs quality management procedures. DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES: 1. Manage a section of site operations. 2. Overall knowledge of construction activities and permanent works. 3. Conduct Internal technical meetings. 4. Cost control, awareness, measures and productivity / monitor and report construction productivity. 5. Permanent and temporary material availability in the local market. 6. Management of plant, equipment, material and labour. 7. Lead a team of site engineers. 8. Project resources planning / short term programmes. 9. Identify and deliver the task in a timely and effective manner. 10. Manage design consultant. 11. Manage and control all site engineering functions. 12. Preparation of bar bending schedules. 13. Construction methods rebar, formwork, concrete. 14. Deal with project managers /consultants. 15. Management of construction / shop drawings. 16. Temporary works design and implementation. 17. Manage - NOC procedures. 18. Clearly relay key/critical project information to site management. 19. Problem solving skills. 20. Produce and monitor material tracking schedules. 21. Implement site QA/QC. 22. Interpret and implement BS, AASHTO, DIN standards. 23. Preparation of ITP's. 24. Maintain site progress records and diaries. 25. Clearly communicate and implement senior management instructions. 26. Manage subcontractors and conducting regular meetings and reviews. 27. Understanding and implementation of QMS procedures. 28. Quantity surveying and estimation. 29. Management of site supervisory staff. 30. Implement site HSE procedures. 31. Communicate site construction procedures. 32. Engineering office and site organization. 33. Produce construction method statements. 34. Raise technical queries. 35. Co-ordinate material deliveries /construction activities. 36. Report preparation. 37. Site inspection with the consultant. 38. Achieve set targets. 39. Work under minimal supervision. 40. Plan construction operations. 41. Monitor and report construction outputs. 42. Co-ordinate and prepare working drawings. 43. Preparation and communication of risk assessments. RequirementsRequirementsBEHAVIORAL COMPETENCIES: 1. Can communicate between other engineers. 2. Can manage internal meetings with other members and staff and sub-contractors 3. Good technical skills and ability to lead a team with particular focus on safety, quality and compliance with contract specifications
4. People management/leadership skills, well-organized, good site administrative skills and self motivated. QUALIFICATIONS:
Minimum Qualifications : Diploma/Bachelor Degree in Engineering Minimum Years of Experience : 5 years
Field of experience : Minimum 5 - 6 years experience About the CompanyAbout the CompanyDutco Balfour Beatty LLC is a major participant in the Middle East construction industries via its activities in a diverse range of construction and engineering related fields. The company, which employs around 13,500 people, is one of the largest civil engineering, building and marine contractors in the UAE and also offers clients the focus and expertise of specialist scaffolding, formwork , interiors and plant. DBB, as is commonly known, was formally incorporated in 1984, following the successful, early completion of the US$4 billion Mina Jebel Ali Port project for the Government of Dubai( formerly known as MJAC ) . Over the years, Dutco Balfour Beatty has evolved into one (more...)
